    <h4 id="sussex-university-and-riken-cbs">Sussex University and RIKEN CBS</h4>
<p>Human behaviour and decision-making are contingent on the uncertainty that an agent has regarding its environment. The world is a dynamic system and its properties are often too many to keep track of. How is an agent affected by unknown and ambiguous information? How can reliable behaviour emerge in the presence of uncertain stimuli?</p>


    
    
